data.content:
Yes — use `Assert.IsInstanceOfType<T>` which asserts the type and gives you the typed reference:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void Create_ReturnsCorrectHandler()
{
    var factory = new HandlerFactory();
    var result = factory.Create("email");

    Assert.IsInstanceOfType<EmailHandler>(result, out var handler);
    Assert.AreEqual("email", handler.Type);
}
```

This fails with a clear message if the type is wrong (instead of an `InvalidCastException`). In MSTest 4.x, it returns the value directly:

```csharp
var handler = Assert.IsInstanceOfType<EmailHandler>(result);
```
